! Revision Tracking

<$checkbox tiddler="$:/config/mblackman/timelord/enabled" field="text" checked="yes" unchecked="no" default="yes"> Enable revision tracking</$checkbox>

//Uncheck before bulk imports, then re-enable when done.//

---

! Filter Mode

Choose how the filter below selects which tiddlers to track.

<$radio tiddler="$:/config/mblackman/timelord/filter-mode" field="text" value="exclude" default="exclude"> ''Exclude mode'' — track everything except tiddlers matching the filter (default).</$radio>

<$radio tiddler="$:/config/mblackman/timelord/filter-mode" field="text" value="include" default="exclude"> ''Include mode'' — track nothing except tiddlers matching the filter.</$radio>

<$reveal type="match" stateTitle="$:/config/mblackman/timelord/filter-mode" text="include" default="exclude">

!! Include Filter

Only tiddlers matching this filter will be tracked:

<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/mblackman/timelord/include-filter" field="text" tag="input" default="" placeholder="e.g. [tag[Journal]]" class="tc-edit-texteditor"/>

//Example: ''[tag[Journal]]'' tracks only tiddlers tagged ~Journal. An empty filter tracks nothing — use the global toggle above instead.//

</$reveal>

<$reveal type="nomatch" stateTitle="$:/config/mblackman/timelord/filter-mode" text="include" default="exclude">

!! Exclude Filter

Tiddlers matching this filter will not be tracked (leave blank to track all):

<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/mblackman/timelord/exclude-filter" field="text" tag="input" default="" placeholder="e.g. [tag[NoTrack]]" class="tc-edit-texteditor"/>

//Example: ''[tag[NoTrack]]'' skips any tiddler tagged ~NoTrack.//

</$reveal>

!! Per-tiddler override

Add a ''`timelord-track`'' field to any tiddler to override the filter for that one tiddler:

* ''`no`'', ''`false`'', ''`0`'' — skip this tiddler regardless of the filter.
* ''`yes`'', ''`true`'', ''`1`'' — track this tiddler regardless of the filter.

---

! Edit Summaries

<$checkbox tiddler="$:/config/mblackman/timelord/edit-summary-enabled" field="text" checked="yes" unchecked="no" default="yes"> Show edit summary field in the editor</$checkbox>

//When enabled, an input field appears below the editor body where you can describe why you made a change. The summary is stored on the revision and shown in the revision list.//

---

! Date Format

Format string used to render revision timestamps in the Revisions panel. Uses TiddlyWiki's [[date format syntax|https://tiddlywiki.com/static/DateFormat.html]].

<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/mblackman/timelord/date-format" field="text" tag="input" default="DDth MMM YYYY at 0hh:0mm" class="tc-edit-texteditor"/>

//Examples: ''DDth MMM YYYY at 0hh:0mm'' (English), ''YYYY-0MM-0DD 0hh:0mm'' (ISO), ''0DD/0MM/YYYY 0hh:0mm'' (DMY).//

Live preview: <$macrocall $name="now" format={{$:/config/mblackman/timelord/date-format}}/>

---

! Diff Size Limit

Maximum reconstructed text length (in characters) before the diff view falls back to showing raw text. Default: 102400 (100&nbsp;KB).

<$edit-text tiddler="$:/config/mblackman/timelord/diff-size-limit" field="text" tag="input" default="102400" class="tc-edit-texteditor"/>

//Guards the UI against lag on pathologically large tiddlers.//

---

! Chain Integrity

Scan every revision chain in the wiki to detect corruption (missing snapshots, patch failures, hash drift). Run ''Verify'' first; ''Repair'' flags unreconstructable revisions with `revision-broken-chain` so the UI can surface them.

<$button>
Verify timelord
<$action-sendmessage $message="tm-verify-revision-chains"/>
</$button>
<$button>
Repair broken chains
<$action-sendmessage $message="tm-repair-revision-chains"/>
</$button>

<$reveal type="nomatch" state="$:/temp/mblackman/timelord/verify-report" text="">
<div class="mblackman-rh-report-box">
<$transclude tiddler="$:/temp/mblackman/timelord/verify-report" mode="block"/>
</div>
</$reveal>
